HEADWORD: Fondus
<hw>Fon`dus"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fondu</ets>, prop. p. p. of <ets>fondre</ets> to melt, blend. See
<er>Found</er> to cast.]</ety> <def>A style of printing calico, paper
hangings, etc., in which the colors are in bands and graduated into each
other.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

